{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0bebd60d-0360-4d5c-bcee-94a7b51cb943","content":"TUnit uses **Microsoft.Testing.Platform** natively, so you need `--treenode-filter` (not `--filter`):\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --treenode-filter \"/**/Contoso.Notifications.Tests.SmsNotificationTests/**\"\n```\n\nThis matches the full `Namespace.Class` node and runs all tests under it (both `SendSms_HealthCheck` and `SendSms_ValidPhone_Succeeds`).\n\n**Key points:**\n- TUnit doesn't use VSTest's `--filter` — it uses MTP's `--treenode-filter` with a path-like syntax (`/Assembly/Namespace.Class/Method`).\n- `**` matches across path segments, so the leading `/**/` skips the assembly node.\n- The trailing `/**` matches all test methods in the class.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3635686c-e6e6-4757-8bb2-d36f2bccde84","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"TUnit uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) natively. For TUnit with MTP, test filtering uses `--treenode-filter` syntax, not the VSTest `--filter` syntax.\n\nThe TUnit treenode filter syntax for filtering by class is:\n```\n/**/*.SmsNotificationTests/**\n```\n\nThe command would be:\n```\ndotnet test --treenode-filter \"/**/*.SmsNotificationTests/**\"\n```\n\nWait, let me reconsider. TUnit 0.6.x uses MTP. The filter syntax for MTP with TUnit uses `--treenode-filter`. The treenode filter path format is:\n\n\n`/assembly/namespace/class/test`\n\nSo to filter by class name `SmsNotificationTests`, I can use either:\n```\ndotnet test --treenode-filter \"/**/*.SmsNotificationTests/**\"\n```\nor more precisely:\n```\ndotnet test --treenode-filter \"/**/SmsNotificationTests/**\"\n```\n\nThe treenode filter uses a path-like syntax where `*` matches within a segment and `**` matches across segments. The structure is typically `/Assembly/Namespace.Class/Method`, so for TUnit the format follows that pattern with the test project and namespace path. Finishing the filter command...","outputTokens":780,"requestId":"A02E:39BFD7:D134D0: